cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the security and privacy aspects of anonymous cryptocurrencies, which are closely related to the fields of cryptography (cs.CR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The proposed scheme involves the use of group signatures, which are commonly used in distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The efficiency of the proposed scheme is also highlighted, which is a key aspect of software engineering (cs.SE).
